// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apocky-PRIME-DIRECTIVE-v3
//
// § engine/main.cssl  —  CSSL-native engine entry-point + game-loop
//                         1440p 144hz hello-triangle composer.
//
// Spec : specs/30_CONTENT_PACKAGE.csl § ASSET-PIPELINE consumer
//        specs/14_BACKEND.csl § HOST-SUBMIT BACKENDS § DYNAMIC-RESOLUTION
//        specs/24_HOST_FFI.csl § CSSL-SIDE WRAPPERS (Cap<Window/Gpu/Time/Input>)
//        specs/04_EFFECTS.csl § Deadline<6944us> @ 144hz pacing
//        specs/12_CAPABILITIES.csl § THE SIX CAPABILITIES (Cap<X>)
//        specs/08_ENGINE.csl § FORWARD+ RENDERER
//        compiler-rs/crates/loa-host/src/lib.rs (port-target)
//
// Slice : T11-W12-E4B · engine_init + run_frame + main · 1440p 144hz.
//
// § THESIS
//   The CSSL-native engine entry-point. ONE source-of-truth per-process :
//
//     fn engine_main() -> Result<(), Error>
//       state = engine_init(144) ?
//       loop : if !engine_run_frame(&mut state)? { break }
//       cleanup
//
//   The composer wires window → device → swapchain → forward+ pipelines →
//   asset-manager → frame-clock into a single EngineState struct. The
//   game-loop body runs at 1440p144 with the canonical Deadline<6944us>
//   marker on the present path.
//
// § PRIME_DIRECTIVE
//   (a) ALL fn entries do caps_check pre-call to FFI-fns
//   (b) ¬ unbounded-loop : engine_main has explicit-running flag · exit-on-close
//   (c) ¬ heap-alloc in engine_run_frame hot-path : the hot-path's Vec<*>
//       buffers are allocated once at engine_init + reused (visible_meshes ·
//       active_lights · pending_loads). Per-frame is zero-alloc by design.
//   (d) 144hz frame-budget enforced via FrameClock + Deadline<6944us> on present
//   (e) ¬ surveillance · ¬ keylogging · ¬ exfil — every input-poll is local
//       Sensitive<Behavioral> per spec/24 § IFC-LABELS
//   ‼ ¬ override · ¬ harm.
//
// § STAGE-0 NOTES
//   1. engine_init is a sequential composer ; each step propagates Err
//      via match-on-Result (until `?`-operator lands in stage-0 parser).
//      // N! flagged ; mechanical migration once `?` lands.
//   2. engine_run_frame returns `Result<bool, Error>` where the bool is
//      `running` (false = window closed). The double-Err shape lets the
//      caller distinguish "frame-error" from "graceful-close".
//   3. engine_main loops on `running` ; bounded by close-event reception
//      AND by a defensive `MAX_FRAMES_DEFENSIVE` upper bound (1<<31 frames)
//      that prevents runaway consoles.
//   4. Forward+ tile-light culling + depth pre-pass + opaque-main +
//      transparent + post-tonemap : the pipelines live in engine/render_forward
//      ; this composer wires them into a frame_idx-threaded submit chain.
//      ‼ render_forward.cssl not yet landed (parallel-agent) — calls below
//      use the SPEC contract per the dispatch-prompt § READ-FIRST. // N!
//      Migration mechanical once render_forward lands.
//   5. ECS allocator (EntityAlloc + ComponentPool) similarly contract-only.
//      // N! flagged.
//
// § INVARIANTS
//   - EngineState.running = true ⇒ window + device + swapchain ALL valid
//   - FrameClock.target_hz == 144 unless engine_init called with override
//   - frame_idx monotonically increases ; matches FrameClock.frame_count
//   - Engine cleanup ALWAYS pairs every successful gpu::device_create with
//     gpu::device_destroy + every window::spawn with window::destroy

